    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Using this plugin, you can display a text widget for any specific category and/or its sub-categories. For example, you want to show different sidebar banners based on different category. It is easy using this plugin. Just create a new widget and select the category.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the plugin through <code>Plugins &gt; Add New &gt; Upload</code> interface or upload to wp-content/plugins directory using FTP.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin once uploaded from the wordpress plugin administration page.</li>\n<li>Go to Appearance -&gt; Widgets. Drag the &#8216;Category Widgets&#8217; to your loved sidebar. You can add as many as you want.</li>\n<li>Fill the form as you expect the output. You&#8217;r done.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>Please visit my blog</h4>\n<p>\n<p>You can ask it <a href=\"http://shailan.com/contact\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">here</a></p>\n</p>\n\n",
